(a) murder or other wilful crime against the person of a Head
of  State  or  a  member  of  the  Head  of  State’s  immediate
family;

(d) that  the  offence  is  of  a  political  character,  or  that  the
proceedings are being taken with a view to try or punish
him  for  an  offence  of  a  political  character;

(c) upon  being  satisfied  that  the  alleged  act  or  omission  of
the fugitive criminal would, if it had taken place in Malaysia,
constitute  an  offence  under  the  laws  of  Malaysia;

(ii) prosecution for the offence in respect of which his
return  is  sought  is  barred  by  time  in  the  country
which  seeks  his  return;

(iii) the offence is an offence under military law which
is not also an offence under the general criminal
law;

(iv) the fugitive criminal has been acquitted or pardoned
by a competent tribunal or authority in the country
which  seeks  his  return  or  in  Malaysia;

(a) any duly authenticated warrant for the arrest of the fugitive
criminal issued by the country which seeks his return or
any  duly  authenticated  copy  of  such  warrant;

(b) any duly authenticated document to provide evidence of
the fugitive criminal’s conviction or sentence or the extent
to  which  a  sentence  imposed  has  not  been  carried  out;

(a) in the case of a requisition made under section 29, issue
a  temporary  surrender  warrant  under  his  hand  and  seal;
or

