for a writ of habeas corpus to review the validity
of  the  decision  to  commit  him  to  prison;

(c) if the certificate of or judicial document stating the fact
of conviction purports to be certified by a Judge, Magistrate
or officer of the country where the conviction took place;

(a) until the expiration of the period of ten days, beginning
with the day on which the order of discharge was made;
or

